PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779019866
OL,3,CWes Streeting confirms he will stand
OL,4,Cin Labour leadership race
OL,6,FHe continued: "Today, Tommy Robinson
OL,7,Fand his followers are marching through
OL,8,Fthe streets of our capital city.
OL,10,F"The last time he did, ministers were
OL,11,Fsent out by No 10 with a media script
OL,12,Fto explain the march, rather than
OL,13,Fcondemn it."
OL,15,FStreeting also condemned the use of
OL,16,Fthe English flag by nationalist and
OL,17,Ffar-right groups, telling his
OL,18,Faudience: "That flag belongs to all of
OL,19,Fus, not just some of us".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1779019866
OL,3,CWes Streeting confirms he will stand
OL,4,Cin Labour leadership race
OL,6,FHe also said of his politics: "You
OL,7,Fwill not always agree with me, but you
OL,8,Fwill always know where I stand."
OL,10,FStreeting resigned from Starmer's
OL,11,Fcabinet on Thursday, following days of
OL,12,Fspeculation that he would launch a
OL,13,Fleadership bid against the prime
OL,14,Fminister.
OL,16,FIn a letter to the PM, Streeting said
OL,17,Fhe was "proud" to have stood alongside
OL,18,FStarmer in the 2024 elections, but
OL,19,Fdescribed the success of Reform in the
OL,20,Flocal elections as an "existential
OL,21,Fthreat to the future integrity".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
